51.6	Andrew_Grove	Andrew Grove	Andrew ("Andy") Stephen Grove (born 2 Sept 1936), is a Hungarian-born Jewish-American businessman, engineer, author, and a science pioneer in the semiconductor industry. He escaped from Communist-controlled Hungary at the age of 20 and moved to the U.S., where he finished his education. He later became CEO of Intel and was a pioneering figure in transforming the company into a giant.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Andrew_Grove.jpg/225px-Andrew_Grove.jpg
